THE SPIRITUAL PLANES
App Pitch & Store Listing Document
For App Developers & Publishers
ONE-SENTENCE PITCH
"Among Us meets the Afterlife" — A social survival game where you play as
a dead spirit trying to figure out who is an ally, who is a predator, and who
is just wounded, using nothing but your discernment.
THE HOOK
You are dead. You didn't make it to the next afterlife. You're stuck in a
liminal space full of spirits — some want to help you, some want to consume
you, and some are so hurt they pretend to be monsters.
No emojis. No labels. No easy answers.
You have to learn to "read" spirits the same way you read people in real life:
by watching their behavior, listening to their patterns, and trusting your gut.
This is not a horror game. This is a spiritual detective game.
WHY THIS WILL WORK
1. The "Among Us" Formula, But Emotional
Among Us proved that social deduction games are massive. But Among Us is about
logical deduction (who vented, who was where). The Spiritual Planes is about
emotional and spiritual discernment — a deeper, more personal form of
deduction that resonates with players on a psychological level.
2. The AI Revolution
With GPT-4 and Claude, we can create NPCs that feel genuinely alive. They
remember. They adapt. They manipulate. They grieve. No two sessions are the same
because the AI generates unique personalities, backstories, and tactics every
time.
3. The Spiritual Market is Underserved
There is no major mobile game that addresses spirituality, the afterlife, and
discernment in a sophisticated way. The market is either:
Horror (Five Nights at Freddy's, Phasmophobia)
Casual (Candy Crush, Wordle)
Action (Call of Duty, PUBG)
There is no thoughtful, narrative-driven, spiritually-themed social game.
This fills that gap.
4. The Meme Potential
The game's premise — "You are dead and surrounded by manipulative spirits" —
is inherently memeable. The "no emojis" rule, the "Wall of God" mechanic, the
"Truth-Teller nobody listens to" — these are all concepts that will spread
organically on TikTok, Twitter, and Reddit.
5. The Replayability
Every session is different because:
AI generates unique entity personalities
Player choices affect future sessions
Multiple endings (Ascend, Stay, Return)
Multiplayer adds human unpredictability
Seasonal events and expansions
